message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper deals with machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and involves training machines to understand and answer questions based on textual input. The paper proposes a data augmentation technique for generating unanswerable questions, which is relevant to NLP tasks such as question-answering and dialogue systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all relevant to the paper's focus on machine learning and neural networks.
